<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-17T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-17T07:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/91: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-17T13:00:00+01:00">February 17, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 17—10:30
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>9. Refer to Department’s telegram No. 4 of February 16.<note n="15" xml:id="d720fn15">Not printed; it stated that the President had sent
                                the supplementary agreement to the Senate on February 14
                                (711.632/89).</note> Today Schober wanted to know what the prospects
                            were of Senate acting this session. Fear that Austrian Government is
                            stalling while awaiting Senate action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>